5000|$|Track {{warrants}} {{are issued}} granting main track use between two named points (i.e. milepost sign, station, and/or any fixed physical point, {{such as a}} switch). The dispatcher may also issue time constraints (known as [...] "Box 6" [...] on a standard form), although the track warrants remain in effect until cleared {{by a member of}} the receiving crew. Track warrants are sometimes used in conjunction with a <b>block</b> <b>signal</b> <b>system</b> to provide rear-end protection against following trains.|$|E
