5000|$|Ashbel Welch (1809-1882) was a {{prominent}} American civil engineer and {{a president of the}} American Society of Civil Engineers (ASCE) in 1882. [...] Welch originated and installed a <b>block</b> <b>signaling</b> <b>system</b> on the Camden and Amboy Railroad between Philadelphia and New Brunswick. First in America, the system later came into use on all American railroads.|$|R
